%global pkg_name composable-associations

%bcond_with tests

Name:           %{pkg_name}
Version:        0.1.0.0
Release:        0
Summary:        Types and helpers for composing types into a single larger key-value type
Group:          Development/Libraries/Haskell

License:        BSD-3-Clause
Url:            https://hackage.haskell.org/package/%{name}
Source0:        https://hackage.haskell.org/package/%{name}-%{version}/%{name}-%{version}.tar.gz

BuildRequires:  ghc-Cabal-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-rpm-macros
%if %{with tests}
BuildRequires:  ghc-lens-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-tasty-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-tasty-hunit-devel
%endif

%description
A library providing generic types and helpers for composing types together into
a a single key-value type.

This is useful when a normalized data model has a denormalized serialization
format. Using this libraries types and functions you build compose your data
into the denormalized key-value format needed for serialization. Other
libraries provide concrete implementations for a given serialization format.


